## Database Schema

```mermaid
erDiagram
    Brand ||--o{ Product : has
    Product ||--o{ Variant : has
    Brand ||--o{ ScrapeJob : triggers

    Brand {
        int id PK
        string name
        string slug
        string base_url
        string logo_url
        datetime created_at
    }

    Product {
        int id PK
        int brand_id FK
        string name
        string url
        string image_url
        float price
        string currency
        string category
        string description
        datetime last_scraped
        datetime created_at
    }

    Variant {
        int id PK
        int product_id FK
        string size
        string color
        string color_hex
        boolean in_stock
        int quantity "nullable, only if site exposes it"
        string sku
    }

    ScrapeJob {
        int id PK
        int brand_id FK
        string status "pending|running|completed|failed"
        int products_found
        int variants_found
        string error_message "nullable"
        datetime started_at
        datetime completed_at
    }
```

### Key design decisions:
- **Variant** stores size/color/stock at the most granular level (e.g., "Size 9, Black, In Stock")
- **ScrapeJob** tracks every scrape run for history and debugging
- Products are **upserted** (update if URL matches, insert if new) so data stays current without duplicates

